\section{Empirical strategies}

This section presents the methodology to investigate the... The main identification strategy is the logistic regression model as following

$$Pr(y_{i}=1|X_{i})=\frac{\mathrm{e}^{\beta_{0}+\beta_{1}X_{i}}}{1+\mathrm{e}^{\beta_{0}+\beta_{1}X_{i}}} $$
in which $y_{i}$ is a dummy variable which equals to 1 if a person participates in job training and 0 otherwise, $X_{i}$ contains all control variables which belong to three groups: (1) demography (migration background, gender, marital status, age, age squared), (2) human capital (years of education, tenure with firms, German language skills) and (3) occupational characteristics (position, firm size, industry, public sector, temporary employment agency, permanent contract). In addition, models also control for dummies of 16 Federal states in Germany, and survey years dummies. 

