\clearpage
      \small
Source: Combined data of GSOEP and IAB-SOEP Migration Sample (Wave: 2014 - 2016), sample weights used.

Notes: This table reports results of the Average Marginal Effects (AMEs) of the logistic regression of on-the-job training participation on people with different migration backgrounds.

Model 1: People with different migration backgrounds.

Model 2: People with different migration backgrounds and demographic variables.

Model 3: People with different migration backgrounds, demographic and human capital variables (exclude German language skills).

Model 4: People with different migration backgrounds, demographic and human capital variables (include German language skills).

Model 5: People with different migration backgrounds, demographic, human capital variables (exclude German language skills), and occupational characteristics.

Model 6: People with different migration backgrounds, demographic, human capital variables (include German language skills), and occupational characteristics.

Ref = Reference category, p: level of significance: * $p < .1$, ** $p < .05$, *** $p < .01$. Standard errors clustered at personal level and reported in parentheses. Percentage of correct prediction estimates assume that if the estimated probability is greater than or equal to $.5$ then the event is expected to occur and not occur otherwise.



